{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "AI holds the potential to enhance democratic and participatory processes by facilitating more accessible methods of preference elicitation and simulating collective preferences (Gudiño-Rosero et al.; 2024; Feffer et al.; 2023).",
    "By simplifying how preferences are gathered, AI can broaden public participation, making it easier for individuals to express their views.",
    "Additionally, AI can augment existing citizens assemblies (McKinney; 2024) or data on political preferences (Feffer et al.; 2023), providing deeper insights into public opinion and supporting more responsive, inclusive decision-making.",
    "Although few works exist at the intersection of futures literacy and AI, emerging studies illustrate how futures literacy can help envision the future of a world with AI and its broader impacts (Liveley; 2022; Leander and Burriss; 2020).",
    "While not very developed as a field yet, the topic of hybrid human-artificial intelligence (Schlobach et al.; 2022) will play a pivotal role in advancing responsible foresight by combining the complementary strengths of both human and machine intelligence."
  ],
